cluster_relations.rel_desc: Hummingbirds are important agents that facilitate pollination.

qualifiers.OtherQualifier: Pollination mode: nectar-feeding visits to flowers

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Sunbirds are important agents that facilitate pollination.

qualifiers.OtherQualifier: Pollination mode: nectar-feeding visits to flowers

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject serves as an active biological agent that enables or carries out the object process (e.g., an animal acting as a pollination agent).
args.justification: In both relations, the subject (a bird pollinator group) is described as an important agent that facilitates the object process (pollination). This is a standard agent–process role relation, so a single predicate 'acts_as_agent_of_process' accurately and consistently captures that semantics.
args.remark: Specific pollination mode and importance level are already captured as qualifiers and should not be encoded in the canonical predicate.

args.justification: Both relations specify a biological entity (bird pollinator) acting as an agent that carries out or enables a biological/ecological process (pollination). Grouping them under 'biological_agent_of_process_relation' captures this family of agent–process role links.
The core semantics is that the subject acts as an agent performing or enabling the object process, which is best categorized under AGENCY rather than generic CAUSALITY or ASSOCIATION.
